04/08/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- Macedonia's 24-member delegation was the first to arrive in the newly-built Olympic Village, which officially opened Monday (2 August). The country is fielding ten athletes in five events. In all, 202 countries have confirmed their participation in the Athens Olympics, which begin next week.
Also Tuesday, Greek police announced that they have deported 300 illegal immigrants in the past several days. They were among 1,200 illegal aliens picked up on the Greek mainland and on the island of Crete as part of tighter immigration control on the eve of the Olympics. (AP - 04/08/04; DPA, AFP - 03/08/04)
